      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that ending would be easier for everyone is a cruel lie you tell yourself to numb the pain of being alone. Your existence is not a burden to be discarded, but a story that matters to those who love you, even if they are too afraid to say it. You do not have to choose between staying and fading; you can choose to stay and let your presence heal the silence instead of ending it.",
      "source": "target",
